For three centuries, most American barns and homes east of the Mississippi were built of chestnut wood. Once considered a food for the poor, today the nut has been revitalized and its demand outstrips its supply.

Name: Chickpeas
Description: A legume originated in the Middle East. Charlemagne mentions Chickpeas in his Capitulare de Villis. Ground roasted Chickpeas were noted as a German substitute for coffee during the First World War. The liquid extracted from Chickpeas, called aquafaba, can be used as a vegan egg-white replacement.

Name: Taro
